main event: Several unidentified flying objects were reported over Cheyenne, Wyoming on August 7, 1956, by multiple witnesses.
interesting points: Mr. Thomas F. Dewey observed an object approximately 45 feet in diameter while driving and reported the sighting to the Cheyenne Air Defense Sector., Mr. and Mrs. Carl U. Barber saw a bright object hovering and shooting off at high speed in their neighborhood., Witness Paul Trent described a round object with flashing lights that disappeared after hovering., Damage was reported to a vehicle after a UFO allegedly hovered over it and emitted a beam or energy., Multiple photographs were taken by witnesses, although some did not develop clearly due to lighting conditions.
witness description: Various individuals including Mr. Thomas F. Dewey and Mr. and Mrs. Carl U. Barber.
